8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 998,
9 L.D. 1514, “An Act to Change the Laws Regarding Real Estate Appraisers”
10 Amend the amendment by striking out all of section 1 and inserting the following:
11 'Sec. 1. 32 MRSA §14011, sub-§2, as amended by PL 2007, c. 402, Pt. GG, §3, is
12 further amended to read:
13 2. Members. The board consists of 7 9 members appointed by the Governor. Each
14 member must be a resident of this State. The board consists of:
15 A. Two public members as defined in Title 5, section 12004‑A; and
16 B. Five members who hold valid appraiser licenses, including at least one member
17 who holds a certified general license. and one member who holds a certified residential
18 real property appraiser license;
19 C. One member who is actively engaged in the business of real estate brokerage as
20 defined in section 13001, subsection 2; and
21 D. One member who is actively engaged in the business of banking, including lending
22 for the purpose of buying real property, or who is actively engaged in the mortgaging
23 of real property as governed by Title 33, chapter 9.'
24 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
25 section number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment amends Committee Amendment "A." The amendment modifies the
2288 provision of law governing membership of the Board of Real Estate Appraisers within the
2299 Department of Professional and Financial Regulation as follows.
30 1. It removes changes made by the bill and the committee amendment with respect to
31 public members and retains the language that exists under current law.
32 2. It clarifies that one member must hold a certified residential real porperty appraiser
33 license and removes from the committee amendment the requirement that the member hold
34 that license at the time of the member's appointment to the board.
